---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Laura | AIlchemy"
  description="I'm Laura — Scottish founder, strategist, and builder. This is where I share the recipes, learnings, and processes behind building with AI."
>
  <div class="about-page">

    <div class="about-header">
      <div class="about-header-inner">
        <div class="about-text-col">
          <div class="about-tag">About</div>
          <h1>I'm Laura, and I am a human.</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-photo-col">
        <img src="/laura.png" alt="Laura" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-body">
      <div class="about-content">

        <p class="lead">
          If I were to describe myself, I'd say I'm a Scottish founder, strategist and builder.
          Those are the labels that make sense in work. Underneath them, I'm creative,
          purpose-driven, and always interested in what becomes possible when the right idea
          meets the right tools and the right people.
        </p>

        <h2>The name</h2>
        <p>
          The name AIlchemy came from the meeting point between AI and alchemy. Long before the word
          became shorthand for turning lead into gold, alchemy was a strange and fascinating
          collision of metalwork, medicine, philosophy and spirituality. It emerged from a view of
          the world in which matter was not fixed or empty, but alive with meaning. To change a
          substance was not only a technical act. It was part of a wider belief that nature itself
          was always in motion, always changing, always becoming.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is what still draws me to the idea. Alchemy began with the belief that transformation
          is built into reality.
        </p>

        <h2>That feels relevant now</h2>
        <p>
          I see AIlchemy at work every day in the way people learn, build, test, rethink and create
          with new tools. In the moment someone moves from scratching their head to an aha. In the
          decision to stay open instead of defensive. In the discipline of taking an idea, working it
          properly, and turning it into something useful.
        </p>
        <p>
          By doing that work myself, I know what the journey asks of you.
        </p>

        <h2>What this is</h2>
        <p>
          This is where I share the recipes, the learnings, and the processes behind that work.
          It's a place for ideas in motion, better ways of thinking, and practical ways of building.
          Some of it will be strategic. Some of it will be creative. Some of it will simply be me
          showing my workings so that others can find their own way through.
        </p>
        <p>
          I thrive in periods of change. I know not everyone does. My hope is that this becomes a
          place where AI feels less like a threat at the door and more like something you can sit
          with, understand, and use with intention. A place to learn, to experiment, and to have fun
          without the fear of missing the AI party.
        </p>

        <EmailSignup
          heading="Stay in the loop."
          subtext="New guides, prompts, and tools — when they're ready, not on a schedule."
        />

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-top: 5rem;
  }

  /* ── Header ── */
  .about-header {
    background: var(--deep);
    padding: 5rem 3rem 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
    min-height: 320px;
  }

  .about-header-inner {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    /* leave room on the right for the bleeding photo */
    padding-right: 300px;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .about-tag {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--pink-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: normal;
    color: white;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  /* Photo — bleeds off the right edge, Option B */
  .about-photo-col {
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 280px;
  }

  .about-photo-col img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
    /* Sharp at right + bottom edges (bleeds out), soft radius on top-left only */
    border-radius: 12px 0 0 0;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top center;
  }

  /* ── Body ── */
  .about-body {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5.5rem 3rem 5rem;
  }

  .about-content .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  /* Section headings — semibold, generous space, pink accent line */
  .about-content h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--deep);
    margin: 3.5rem 0 1.1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.7rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .about-content h2::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--pink);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* ── Mobile ── */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .about-header {
      padding: 4rem 1.5rem 0;
      min-height: unset;
    }

    .about-header-inner {
      padding-right: 0;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    /* On mobile, photo sits below the heading, inline */
    .about-photo-col {
      position: static;
      width: 160px;
      margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    }

    .about-photo-col img {
      border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
    }

    .about-body {
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
